column2: Windy- difficult to stay on location.
Choppy waves- difficult to hold position.
Beautiful; Pollen decreased;  Beginning of fast boating time
very warm weather; heron on the beach

column1: Lake level lower- but usual for this time of year

column2: Weeds high in some area.  consistently seeing a small

column1: loon for a couple of hours in the early evening near the sampling area.  The water color was actually kind of a greenish-brown- but pretty clear- not blue.

column2: Nice sunny early fall day- light breeze
There's actually very little color to the water- just

column1: Still seeing a lonely loon in the evening.  Very little boating now

column2: This was done the day after Memorial weekend holiday.
Breezy day + partly cloudy.  Little activity on lake
Some algae( ) collecting in a few places
Extensive hot and dry spell - only .5" rain in last month.
Water appears cloudy in the channels. Saw a loon- blue
There was about a 3 ft. algae mass at our water's edge.  Mallard families seen swimming + on our shore.  The loons have been vocal lately.
Measurement done on a Monday after a busy weekend of activity.  Two apparently none resident loons on lake.  Water is the lowest I've seen in many years.

Heron on our beach.  No loons seen or heard on Blacksmith for more than a week.  Saw many jellyfish (now that I know what they look like!)  Water level is extremely low; haven't seen it this low in 20 years
Water is exceptionally low.  Eurasian water milfoil is thick in front of our beach.  One loon seen last week.
Lots of minnows + small fish by shore; a mallard drake cruised the shore + a solitary loon kept me company
one loon seen preening and fishing
Eurasian Water Milfoil treatment was very effective in this basin
1.5 inches rain previous nite after prolonged dry spell
Cloudy day. Sunday reading; average weekend boat traffic
Few jellyfish seen in Blacksmith this season.
Sunny + breezy- light boat traffic- one loon fishing
typical busy Sunday on the lake.  Sunny- few clouds.
Calm- sunny day; minimal boat activity.  Two loons seen consistently on lake- but no chicks.
Haven't seen or heard the loons for about a week
Breezy- partly cloudy nice day.   One loon seen.
We scared up a heron and an mature eagle while we were on the lake.   Two loons flew overhead.   Nice day- partly cloudy + breezy- no traffic to speak of on the lake.
Partly cloudy day with lots of Sunday boat traffic
I just recently learned that one of the two loons that I'd been seeing was killed apparently by a boat on the July 4th weekend.
beautiful cool afternoon; partly cloudy + calm
A nice relatively calm day of wind.
Sunny breezy day after a busy holiday weekend
I haven't seen any jelly fish since( ) the major EWM treatment
calm- overcast day.  Loons were making quite a racket on 6/7 at 10 PM
Light breezy day with a lot of pollen in the water.  Also observed a loon preening.
foggy- misty- and a little breeze.
Warm + humid- sunny- light breeze.  One loon heard calling overhead.

sunny + breezy. I had a hard time getting the anchor started up.   When it got to the surface the first 3 ft of the rope was covered with a black sediment ( ).  It was  black as grease.  I was able to remove most of it in the water with slight rubbing. sunny + breezy. I had a hard time getting the anchor started up.   When it got to the surface the first 3 ft of the rope was covered with a black sediment ( ).  It was  black as grease.  I was able to remove most of it in the water with slight rubbing.
Mostly sunny- slight breeze- after a 49 degree evening. Monday after a busy weekend and the water is calm.
Partly Cloudy- 60 degrees F- Light Wind.
Sunny- few clouds- clear sky- and quiet water.
Sunny with slight overcast and slight breeze.
Somewhat hazy day off + on.  Done the day after a busy weekend.  Hot.
Cloudy with breeze from the NE. Water color greenish and clear with normal water levels. First dissolved oxygen testing after an extended period of warm weather.
warm- sunny day with a light breeze.  The water isn't perfectly clear like it sometimes is- but still very nice.  Only "wildlife" was a pilot practicing aerobatics.
Mostly calm.  2 loons hanging around much of the day. Little boat traffic

Sunny- few clouds- clear- quiet morning- thin layer of fog across water- very calm.  Fewer sightings of freshwater jellyfish.  The water level is 1in. below normal- the water color is greenish and the clarity is clear.
Busy holiday weekend. Beautiful weather.  Loons were vocal yesterday morning + saw an adult and chick on Pestigo basin of Legend Lake
A calm- cool day between the rains.  Helper: Karl Richter
Water color greenish/blue. Weather was sunny but partly cloudy. Other helpers: Arland Dillenburg.
2 adult loons and 2 chicks which seem to be inhabiting this lake seen again this afternoon in front.  They were braving all the boat traffic over the holiday.
Partly Cloudy- Warm- but slight breeze.
still have a loon pair and 2 chicks on Big Blacksmith
Humid- Partly cloudy morning- 4 loons fishing for breakfast.breeze out of the Northwest....
Adult loon with 2 immature loons sighted.  Eagle overhead.
Partly Cloudy- humid- lots of rain this morning....
Beautiful day- slight breeze- calm.  Have not seen any loons on this lake this year contrary to previous years.
The water was not as clear as it usually was; a little cloudy.  I was surprised that I could see the Secchi disk as far as I could- considering.

column1: 2 adult loons and one chick seen.
Overcast day- calm.  Brief shower earlier.

column2: Hot- Sunny- a little wind.   No boat  traffic.
Beautiful calm morning.  Loons calling overhead.  Loon + chick seen
No Wind Sunny No boat Traffic at all.
Quite breezy + mostly cloudy.  Tiny particles in the water.  1 juvenile loon still here.
Sunny warm breeze.  Fresh water Jellyfish everywhere.
Sunny- Clear- Nice-  Water Color Greenish
Busy Saturday on the lake.  One loon with 1 chick seen.  Also- 2 globs of algae seen off properties 35-36 Highlands addition.  One oval-ish 5-6' long and one smaller close by.

column1: One eurasian milfoil plant seen by 39 Highlands.

column2: Partly Sunny- Breeze from East to West-  Greenish Water

2 loons seen and heard.  Also- advised 2 adults on a jet ski who buzzed a loon about the proper distance to keep from loons.  Sunny- slight breeze- little boat traffic for July.  Saw a big fish jump/splash from across the lake on 7-22-15
Hot- Clear- Bright Sun -  Water Greenish and Brownish
Clear- Hot-  Water Clear-  Light Browish Color....
Cool- Cloudy- Windy 10MPH   water Color Brownish

column1: Water clear and Brownish with Jellyfish present.

column2: Sunny morning- calm- few people out fishing- no clouds in sight. saw a loon

Sunny day.  Some pollen floating on the surface.  The water is not crystal clear- but it's not murky either.  Female mallard and ducklings swimming/feeding at our beach front.  I've heard a loon- but haven't seen one yet on this basin.
Moderate boat traffic at the beginning of the holiday weekend. Partly cloudy
Sunny.  One loon present.  Much EWM along ours + neighbors beach.
partly cloudy- strong northeastern winds- saw loon
Pleasant weather- light breeze.  One loon seen and several geese with babies Pleasant weather- light breeze.  One loon seen and several geese with babies. Lots of pollen collecting near shore.
Beautiful  afternoon; partly cloudy.  2 loon families seen. One pair with 2 chicks on Big Blacksmith and one pair with 2 chicks on Spring Lake basin.
Beautiful day; little boat traffic this week
partly  cloudy- scattered storms.  one loon seen
Cloudy- sun trying to peek through- saw paddle boaters. Ryan and Zach collected data. Cloudy- sun trying to peek out- paddle boaters seen. Collected by Ryan and Zach.
very warm- slight breeze.  A lot of pollen in the lake.  2 loons seen in the other basins. Midweek- no traffic.
Done on a Monday after a busy weekend.  Calm. One loon pair + chick seen.  Haven't seen any jellyfish this year (or last either).  Much EWM in front of our our's and neighbors's houses.
Bright Sunshine- calm breeze- smooth water. Hundreds of minnows at the surface. Several people fishing. Many fish jumping.
A lot of pollen on the lake and EWM in our lakefront.
Overcast with light breeze. Several boats out fishing.
Clear skies and calm. Saw two adult loons and a baby.
Nice day- partly cloudy- light breeze.  We have a pair of loons with 2 chicks regularly seen in front.  Less traffic on the lake this week.
Cold- 62 degrees. Wind 8 to 12 mph and cloudy. Saw 2 loons.
I believe that the adult loons have left.  We still have many hummingbirds around our feeders.

column1: The EWM is very thick + topping the water in front of our lot and the neighbors.

column2: Very calm water. Overcast and foggy. Loons on the water.
H. Mandel-C. Scherer-J. Albers-J. Ireland-R. Towne
